title: My Chemical Romance Bring “Black Parade” Tour to San Francisco: Photo Gallery
description: The emo greats played their beloved 2006 album in full and a second set of hits at Oracle Park. My Chemical Romance Bring “Black Parade” Tour to San Francisco: Photo Gallery Consequence Staff
author: Consequence Staff
excerpt: My Chemical Romance played their beloved 2006 album, Welcome to the Black Parade, and a second set of hits at Oracle Park in San Francisco. See our photo gallery.
text: A week after kicking off the “Long Live: The Black Parade North American Tour”  with a thrilling show in Seattle, My Chemical Romance made their way to Oracle Park in San Francisco, California, on Saturday night. Our photographer Raymond Ahner was on the scene and you can see his exclusive photo gallery below. Get My Chemical Romance Tickets Here After opening the show with a full performance of their 2006 emo classic Welcome to the Black Parade — complete with a choreographed stage show — MCR delivered a second set packed with greatest hits and fan favorites. The San Francisco setlist differed significantly from the Seattle tour kickoff, as the band played songs such as “Thank You for the Venom,” “Summertime,” “Boy Division,” and “The Kids From Yesterday,” along with a cover of The Smashing Pumpkins’ “Bullet With Butterfly Wings.”My Chemical Romances’ “Black Parade” tour will next hit Los Angeles, with dates still ahead in Arlington, TX; East Rutherford, NJ; Philadelphia, PA; Toronto, ON; Chicago, IL; Boston, MA; and Tampa, FL. Fans can look for tickets to MCR’s sold-out Black Parade concerts here. My Chemical Romance – “Black Parade” San Francisco Setlist: The Black Parade The End. Dead! html:
A week after kicking off the “Long Live: The Black Parade North American Tour”  with a thrilling show in Seattle, My Chemical Romance made their way to Oracle Park in San Francisco, California, on Saturday night. Our photographer Raymond Ahner was on the scene and you can see his exclusive photo gallery below.

Get My Chemical Romance Tickets Here

After opening the show with a full performance of their 2006 emo classic Welcome to the Black Parade — complete with a choreographed stage show — MCR delivered a second set packed with greatest hits and fan favorites. The San Francisco setlist differed significantly from the Seattle tour kickoff, as the band played songs such as “Thank You for the Venom,” “Summertime,” “Boy Division,” and “The Kids From Yesterday,” along with a cover of The Smashing Pumpkins’ “Bullet With Butterfly Wings.”

My Chemical Romances’ “Black Parade” tour will next hit Los Angeles, with dates still ahead in Arlington, TX; East Rutherford, NJ; Philadelphia, PA; Toronto, ON; Chicago, IL; Boston, MA; and Tampa, FL. Fans can look for tickets to MCR’s sold-out Black Parade concerts here.
